  "prompt": "What are some places to visit enroute Chennai to Pondicherry?",
  "response": "Traveling from Chennai to Pondicherry is a scenic journey along the East Coast Road (ECR), offering several interesting places to visit. Here are some must-see stops en route:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Kovalam Beach**\n- A serene and less crowded beach, ideal for relaxation and water sports.\n- Located near Mahabalipuram, it's a great spot to enjoy the sea breeze.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Mahabalipuram (Mamallapuram)**\n- A UNESCO World Heritage Site known for its ancient rock-cut temples and structures.\n- Key attractions:\n  - Shore Temple\n  - Five Rathas (Pancha Rathas)\n  - Arjuna\u2019s Penance\n  - Krishna\u2019s Butterball\n\n---\n\n### **3. DakshinaChitra**\n- A living museum showcasing the art, architecture, and culture of South India.\n- Features traditional houses, crafts, and performances from Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Karnataka, and Andhra Pradesh.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Alamparai Fort**\n- A ruined 18th-century fort located near Kadapakkam.\n- Offers picturesque views of the lagoon and the Bay of Bengal.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Marakkanam Salt Pans**\n- A unique landscape of salt pans where you can witness the process of salt harvesting.\n- A great spot for photography.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Cholamandal Artists\u2019 Village**\n- An artsy community near Chennai promoting contemporary Indian art.\n- Features galleries and workshops by local artists.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Auroville**\n- A universal township near Pondicherry, known for its spiritual and sustainable living.\n- Key attractions:\n  - Matrimandir\n  - Auroville Beach\n  - Visitor Center\n\n---\n\n### **8. Pichavaram Mangrove Forest**\n- Located near Chidambaram, it\u2019s one of the largest mangrove forests in the world.\n- Offers boating through lush green waterways.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Chidambaram Nataraja Temple**\n- A famous temple dedicated to Lord Shiva as Nataraja, the cosmic dancer.\n- Known for its architectural grandeur and spiritual significance.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Paradise Beach (Pondicherry)**\n- A pristine beach accessible by boat from Chunnambar Boat House.\n- Perfect for swimming and relaxation.\n\n---\n\nThese stops make the journey from Chennai to Pondicherry a memorable experience, blending history, culture, and natural beauty.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
